    {
      "title": "Doubly Weak Verbs (الفعل اللفيف)",
      "titleArabic": "الفعل اللفيف",
      "content": [
        "Doubly weak verbs (الفعل اللفيف) have two weak letters (و or ي) among their radicals. There are two types based on the position of the weak letters.",
        "اللفيف المقرون has weak letters adjacent (positions 2 and 3). اللفيف المفروق has weak letters separated (positions 1 and 3)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "اللفيف المقرون: weak letters in positions 2 and 3 (e.g., طَوَى، رَوَى، كَوَى)",
        "اللفيف المفروق: weak letters in positions 1 and 3 (e.g., وَفَى، وَعَى، وَقَى)",
        "These verbs combine rules from both hollow and defective verbs",
        "طَوَى (to fold) - root ط-و-ي",
        "وَفَى (to fulfill) - root و-ف-ي"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "وَفَى بِوَعْدِهِ", "english": "He fulfilled his promise" },
        { "arabic": "رَوَى الْقِصَّةَ", "english": "He narrated the story" },
        { "arabic": "طَوَى الثَّوْبَ", "english": "He folded the garment" },
        { "arabic": "وَعَى الدَّرْسَ", "english": "He understood the lesson" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Conjugation of Doubly Weak Verbs",
      "titleArabic": "تصريف الفعل اللفيف",
      "content": [
        "Doubly weak verbs require careful attention to both weak letters during conjugation."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "وَفَى → يَفِي (he fulfills) - combines مثال and ناقص rules",
        "طَوَى → يَطْوِي (he folds)",
        "رَوَى → يَرْوِي (he narrates)",
        "Past tense with pronouns: وَفَيْتُ، طَوَيْتُ، رَوَيْتُ"
      ]
    }
  ],
